# -*- encoding: utf-8 -*-
# Arc: UnionKingdom | Scene: UnionKingdom9intermezzo1
# Source: C:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\steamapps\common\The Survival of Sarah Rose\game\script.rpy

translate ru strings:

    old "As the tiresome work dragged one, Sarah lifted her head from her desk."
    new "As the tiresome work dragged one, Sarah lifted her head from her desk."

    old "Time had passed and turned and by now she worked by candlelight."
    new "Time had passed and turned and by now she worked by candlelight."

    old "When the words and letters on the pages began to shift and twist, she knew she had reached her limit."
    new "When the words and letters on the pages began to shift and twist, she knew she had reached her limit."

    old "Sarah fell back in her chair and turned her eyes towards the ceiling."
    new "Sarah fell back in her chair and turned her eyes towards the ceiling."

    old "Even the ceiling seemed to dance."
    new "Even the ceiling seemed to dance."

    old "Sarah closed her eyes."
    new "Sarah closed her eyes."

    old "Slowly, a peace came over her."
    new "Slowly, a peace came over her."

    old "So far from home. So isolated. Alone."
    new "So far from home. So isolated. Alone."

    old "There were her soldiers. Her servants. Her attendants."
    new "There were her soldiers. Her servants. Her attendants."

    old "She was not truly alone, but all the people that meant most to her in the world were so very distant."
    new "She was not truly alone, but all the people that meant most to her in the world were so very distant."

    old "Somehow, being surrounded by people only seemed to make her feel more lonely."
    new "Somehow, being surrounded by people only seemed to make her feel more lonely."

    old "But with her eyes closed, she could dream easy."
    new "But with her eyes closed, she could dream easy."

    old "And things like time and place meant so very little."
    new "And things like time and place meant so very little."

    old "Her husband. Her children."
    new "Her husband. Her children."

    old "When she held her eyes closed, Sarah could swear they were so close she could reach out to them."
    new "When she held her eyes closed, Sarah could swear they were so close she could reach out to them."

    old "She opened her eyes and looked at the desk again."
    new "She opened her eyes and looked at the desk again."

    old "Suddenly, she reached over and grabbed one of the blank pages."
    new "Suddenly, she reached over and grabbed one of the blank pages."

    old "Placing it in front of her, pressed the tip of her pen to the paper and began to write."
    new "Placing it in front of her, pressed the tip of her pen to the paper and began to write."

    old "Dear husband."
    new "Dear husband."

    old "I write you from my study in Queen Maeiv's castle."
    new "I write you from my study in Queen Maeiv's castle."

    old "All my needs have thus far been well seen to. The room. The celebrations. The beautiful gardens."
    new "All my needs have thus far been well seen to. The room. The celebrations. The beautiful gardens."

    old "Yet rather than enjoying any of them, I find myself only saddened."
    new "Yet rather than enjoying any of them, I find myself only saddened."

    old "Once I walked this world by myself, and all that I saw and loved were my own to cherish."
    new "Once I walked this world by myself, and all that I saw and loved were my own to cherish."

    old "But now, I find myself haunted by you, even as we are countless distances removed."
    new "But now, I find myself haunted by you, even as we are countless distances removed."

    old "As I walk the gardens, I find myself instinctually looking over my shoulder."
    new "As I walk the gardens, I find myself instinctually looking over my shoulder."

    old "To see you. Look for you. Share a glance and moment."
    new "To see you. Look for you. Share a glance and moment."

    old "It is odd to me, even after all these years, that I can speak more with you in a gesture than I can speak with most in a conversation."
    new "It is odd to me, even after all these years, that I can speak more with you in a gesture than I can speak with most in a conversation."

    old "Before you, I never had what we now have."
    new "Before you, I never had what we now have."

    old "I never missed, what now so pains me."
    new "I never missed, what now so pains me."

    old "You were an absence for most of my early days, but it is only now that I can feel the absence in my heart."
    new "You were an absence for most of my early days, but it is only now that I can feel the absence in my heart."

    old "If my position were different, I would call upon the guards and make way for home this instant."
    new "If my position were different, I would call upon the guards and make way for home this instant."

    old "To see you. To see our children. To be home, in every sense."
    new "To see you. To see our children. To be home, in every sense."

    old "But duty has yoked each of us apart from one another."
    new "But duty has yoked each of us apart from one another."

    old "And so, again, I sit here writing to you from this cold and lifeless study."
    new "And so, again, I sit here writing to you from this cold and lifeless study."

    old "Longing to fall asleep so that I may sooner begin to dream. In my dreams, I am home."
    new "Longing to fall asleep so that I may sooner begin to dream. In my dreams, I am home."

    old "My dreams, where I can see and smell and touch every part of you, as though we were never seperated."
    new "My dreams, where I can see and smell and touch every part of you, as though we were never seperated."

    old "Even just the thought of your hands on my body solicit from me a reaction."
    new "Even just the thought of your hands on my body solicit from me a reaction."

    old "My own attempts to imitate your touch with my own hands, leave me yearning only for the real thing."
    new "My own attempts to imitate your touch with my own hands, leave me yearning only for the real thing."

    old "Each night when I touch myself, my only fantasies are memories of our encounters."
    new "Each night when I touch myself, my only fantasies are memories of our encounters."

    old "I sketch you from memory, your arms, your chest, your shoulders."
    new "I sketch you from memory, your arms, your chest, your shoulders."

    old "Every part of you."
    new "Every part of you."

    old "And yet no joy or pleasure can rival the truth of you."
    new "And yet no joy or pleasure can rival the truth of you."

    old "Varga."
    new "Varga."

    old "Each peak tasts only of after-climax, as I try to take comfort in the hollow imitation."
    new "Each peak tasts only of after-climax, as I try to take comfort in the hollow imitation."

    old "Instead, I find myself only more desperate to be re-united with you."
    new "Instead, I find myself only more desperate to be re-united with you."

    old "To again press my hands on yours. Your lips on mine."
    new "To again press my hands on yours. Your lips on mine."

    old "Every day and night. No matter time or distance. I am forever yours."
    new "Every day and night. No matter time or distance. I am forever yours."

    old "Dreaming of you..."
    new "Dreaming of you..."

    old "Yours, forever, Sarah."
    new "Yours, forever, Sarah."

    old "Sarah quickly folded the letter, placed it in an envelop and sealed it with her royal seal."
    new "Sarah quickly folded the letter, placed it in an envelop and sealed it with her royal seal."

    old "It would travel across the continent, into the hands of the only man who had any right to see it."
    new "It would travel across the continent, into the hands of the only man who had any right to see it."

